home  reservoir capital group reservoir capital group is a privately held investment firm with a flexible opportunistic investment approach reservoir capital group reservoir was founded in  based upon the belief that patient capital and a flexible investment mandate are competitive advantages in the pursuit of superior longterm riskadjusted returns reservoirs primary investment objective is to identify or create investment opportunities with asymmetric riskreward profiles  generally offering enhanced downside protection and meaningful upside optionality these investment opportunities are frequently found in outoffavor areas experiencing fundamental change andor scarcity of capital we also believe a large portion of investment returns are generated by allocating assets to the most attractive asset classes or sectors at opportune times and that partnering with worldclass managers and specialists may provide enhanced riskreward profiles superior economics and proprietary deal flow daniel h stern and craig a huff cochief executive officers and gregg m zeitlin a senior managing director founded reservoir and have worked together as a team for more than nineteen years including their prior tenure managing ziff brothers investments the founders are joined by matthew t popoli and anil a ranavat senior managing directors who have been with reservoir since  in leading reservoirs general investment efforts about us  reservoir capital group about us reservoir was founded in  based upon the belief that patient capital and a flexible investment mandate are competitive advantages in the pursuit of superior longterm riskadjusted returns reservoirs primary investment objective is to identify or create investment opportunities with asymmetric riskreward profiles  generally offering enhanced downside protection and meaningful upside optionality these investment opportunities are frequently found in outoffavor areas experiencing fundamental change andor scarcity of capital reservoir opportunistically invests directly in securities and structured private investments builds platform companies with industry specialists and creates new hedge funds and private equity firms in which the reservoir funds hold ownership or other economic interests reservoir currently has over  billion of capital under management daniel h stern and craig a huff cochief executive officers and gregg m zeitlin a senior managing director founded reservoir and have worked together as a team for more than twentyone years including their prior tenure managing ziff brothers investments the founders are joined by senior managing directors matthew t popoli anil a ranavat and eric engler in leading reservoirs investment efforts reservoir has pursued its opportunistic strategy since  initially with the launch of the opportunistic fund and subsequently with select capital raisings based on the opportunity set  reservoir founded launch of opportunistic fund evergreen hybrid investment fund  reservoircontourglobal coinvestment fund established to invest alongside the opportunistic fund in contourglobal the power platform company  reservoir strategic partners fund hedge fund seeding focus with pelike structure  reservoir resource partners fund natural resources and power focus with pe structure oregon taps reservoir capital for new b energy fund  pe hub subscribe to pe hub wire join over  of your peers get the mustread email for pevc professionals delivered to your inbox daily — for free us edition daily canada edition weekly we will not send you spam and we dont share your email address with rd parties i accept the terms and conditions subscribe yes no registersign in a community for professionals in private capital oregon taps reservoir capital for new b energy fund august   by gregory roth the oregon investment council which manages  billion in state funds has pledged  million to reservoir capital group’s debut energy and resources fund reservoir resource partners lp according to buyouts pehub’s sister magazine the fund plans to invest in energy natural resources and power generation companies the firm is seeking to raise  billion according to the council’s description of the fund the firm has delivered an overall net irr of more than  percent over its year existence  reservoir capital manages around  billion across three funds the new investment is the firm’s second from oregon investment council which committed  million to reservoir strategic partners lp a hedge fund of funds that makes seed investments in new and emerging hedge fund managers a spokesman for reservoir capital was unable to comment on the new fund within the energy space reservoir capital’s new fund is earmarked for power generation which will make up roughly twothirds of the fund’s investments the remaining third is expected to consist of midstream and downstream energy infrastructure assets according to the council’s description torreycove capital partners the council’s private equity adviser wrote that the firm “expects opportunities…to arise in europe given the fact that european utilities are in a distressed position and the fact that european power markets continue to undergo significant change” reservoir capital typically protects against downside risk by taking senior positions in a company’s debt capital structure while making sure that investments are convertible to equity if a company’s operating performance exceeds expectations as part of its commitment oregon investment council was able to negotiate a concession on how its management fee is assessed  the “standard management fee” will be paid only on invested capital not committed capital which is more common this said the council “can help mitigate the traditional ‘jcurve’ associated with most private market fund structures the fund will have a traditional carry reservoir capital was started in  and was cofounded by daniel stern and craig huff who are cochief executives and gregg zeitlin a senior managing director 